    "body": "this is rather a ethers-solc issue, \r\nI wonder why this is not supported, because we already include the test folder when reading all sources:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/gakonst/ethers-rs/blob/fab30887a2373d260d41689e71242ce0ac979c80/ethers-solc/src/config.rs#L90-L101\r\n\r\nwhich is called here https://github.com/gakonst/ethers-rs/blob/master/ethers-solc/src/lib.rs#L208\r\n\r\nand the test folder should be \"test\" by default, hmm\r\n\r\n> Forge implicitly assumes the configured test path is a subdirectory of the configured src path. \r\n\r\nI'm not sure about this, but it could be that we're not setting the tests folder correctly in the `config` crate when the `ProjectPathsConfig` is created.\r\n\r\nhopefully this is enough context, lmk if smth is unclear",
